Comparison of Classification and Clustering Algorithms on Iris Dataset Using R

Talha Hanif Butt

library(caret)
library(mclust)
library(fpc)
library(cluster)
library(clusteval)
library(factoextra)
library(ggplot2)
library(kmed)

Loading Iris Dataset

# attach the iris dataset to the environment
data(iris)
# rename the dataset
dataset <- iris

Partitioning Data for Validation

# create a list of 80% of the rows inthe original dataset we can use for training
validation_index <- createDataPartition(dataset$Species, p=0.80, list=FALSE)
# select 20% of the data for validation
validation <- dataset[-validation_index,]
# use the remaining 80% of data to training and testing the models
dataset <- dataset[validation_index,]

Applying Classification Algorithms on Iris Data

# Run algorithms using 10-fold cross validation
control <- trainControl(method="cv", number=10)
metric <- "Accuracy"
# kNN
set.seed(7)
fit.knn <- train(Species~., data=dataset, method="knn", metric=metric, trControl=control)
# SVM
set.seed(7)
fit.svm <- train(Species~., data=dataset, method="svmRadial", metric=metric, trControl=control)
# Random Forest
set.seed(7)
fit.rf <- train(Species~., data=dataset, method="rf", metric=metric, trControl=control)

Comparison of the Classification Algorithms

# summarize accuracy of models
results <- resamples(list(knn=fit.knn, svm=fit.svm, rf=fit.rf))
summary(results)

Applying Clustering Algorithms

rr # K-means set.seed(20) fit.kmeans <- kmeans(iris[, 0:4], 3, nstart = 20) # Hierarchical Agglomerative set.seed(20) d <- dist(iris[,0:4], method = ) # distance matrix fit.ha <- hclust(d, method=.D) # K-Medoids Clustering num <- as.matrix(iris[,0:4]) mrwdist <- distNumeric(num, num, method = ) fit.kmedoids <- fastkmed(mrwdist, ncluster = 3, iterate = 50)

Getting insights from Hierarchical Agglomerative Clustering

rr # Cut tree into 4 groups sub_grp <- cutree(fit.ha, k = 3) # Number of members in each cluster table(sub_grp)

sub_grp
 1  2  3 
50 64 36

rr ## sub_grp

rr plot(fit.ha, cex = 0.6) rect.hclust(fit.ha, k = 3, border = 2:5)

rr fviz_cluster(list(data = iris[,0:4], cluster = sub_grp))

Conclusion

With better accuracy and kappa measures, KNN has outperformed other competitors on Iris Dataset while Hierarchical Agglomerative Clustering is the winner when compared with K-Means and K-Medoids Clustering on Iris Dataset as it has clustered data better evident from the Cluster Plot and Cluster Dendrogram.
